{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"af4b512c-1b22-40d0-833c-6a36bd5aa623","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName);\n}\n```\n\n**Why modernize:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` passes if *any* line throws, masking bugs (e.g., the constructor could throw instead of `CreateUser`).\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` pinpoints the exact call and lets you assert on exception details like `ParamName` or `Message`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"92839534-80ef-45f4-8e53-4ef3035ab11b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a general knowledge question — no need to explore the codebase.","outputTokens":248,"requestId":"9834:C2332:108A92E:14C471F:69FFDFCC"},"id":"a44fee31-7f75-44f9-af08-0cb6a77937da","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:30:58.807Z","parentId":"d3c7dfa9-0eab-4161-914c-e182d43ec0b3"}
